{{Other uses|Yass (disambiguation){{!}}Yass}}
{{Infobox Software|name=YASS|latest_release_version=1.14|operating_system=[[Linux]], [[Apple Macintosh|Mac]], [[MS-Windows]]|genre=[[Bioinformatics]] tool|licence=[[GNU General Public License|GPLv2]] [[CeCILL]]|website=[http://bioinfo.cristal.univ-lille.fr/yass/ http://bioinfo.cristal.univ-lille.fr/yass/]}}
'''YASS'''<ref name="NoeKucherov2005">{{cite journal |author=Noe L., Kucherov. G.|title=YASS: enhancing the sensitivity of DNA similarity search |journal=Nucleic Acids Research |volume=33|issue=2 |pages=W540–W543 |year=2005 |doi=10.1093/nar/gki478 |pmid=15980530 |pmc=1160238}}</ref><ref name="NoeKucherov2004">{{cite journal |author=Noe L., Kucherov. G.|title=Improved hit criteria for DNA local alignment|journal=BMC Bioinformatics |volume=5 |year=2004 |doi=10.1186/1471-2105-5-149 |pmid=15485572 |pages=149 |pmc=526756}}</ref> is a [[free software]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bioinfo.cristal.univ-lille.fr/yass/files/yass-current/README|accessdate=7 April 2015|title=README}}</ref> pairwise [[sequence alignment software]] for [[nucleotide]] sequences, that is, it can search for similarities between [[DNA]] or [[RNA]] sequences. YASS accepts nucleotide sequences in either plain text or the [[FASTA format]] and the output format includes the [[BLAST]] tabular output. YASS uses several ''transition-constrained'' spaced seed [[k-mer|k-mers]], which allow considerably improved sensitivity. YASS can be used locally on a user's machine, or as [[SaaS]] on the [http://bioinfo.cristal.univ-lille.fr/yass/yass.php YASS web server], which produces a browser based [[Dot plot (bioinformatics)|dot-plot]].
